solution.p:
In mathematics, we use the symbol \Delta (delta) for change in. Thus
\text{distance traveled}\amp= \Delta d = 360-189 = 171 \text{ miles} \text{time elapsed}\amp= \Delta t=4-1=3 \text{ hours} 
Gregor's average speed is the ratio \dfrac{\text{distance traveled}}{\text{time elapsed}} =\dfrac{\Delta d}{\Delta t}, so
\text{Speed}=\frac{\Delta d}{\Delta t} = \frac{171 \text{ miles}}{3 \text{ hours}}= 57 \text{ miles/hour}

authored.pg-code:
$rate = (421-127)/(10-4);
$answer = Compute("$rate");
$units = PopUp(["?",
"miles", 
"hours",
"miles per hour",
"hours per mile"],
  3, 
);

