definition.p:
slope
    \text{slope}=\frac{\text{change in }y\text{-coordinate}}{\text{change in }x\text{-coordinate}} 
    or, in symbols
    m=\frac{\Delta y}{\Delta x}

subsection.p:
In the definition of slope,

    \Delta x~ \text{ is}~ 
        \begin{cases}
        \text{positive if }x\text{ increases} \amp \text{(we move to the right)}\\
        \text{negative if }x\text{ idereases} \amp \text{(we move to the left)}
        \end{cases}


    \Delta y~ \text{ is}~ 
        \begin{cases}
        \text{positive if }y\text{ increases} \amp \text{(we move up)}\\
        \text{negative if }y\text{ dereases} \amp \text{(we move down)}\hphantom{to left}
        \end{cases}

