li.p:
To find an equation for the line, we start with the slope formula,

    m=\frac{y_2 -y_1}{x_2 - x_1}

We substitute \dfrac{-3}{4}  for the slope, m, and (1,-4)  for (x_1,y_1) . For the second point, (x_2,y_2) , we substitute the variable point (x,y)  to obtain

    m=\frac{y + 4}{x-1}

subsection.p:
When we use the slope formula to find the equation of a line, we substitute a variable point (x, y) for the second point. This version of the formula,
m = \frac{y - y_1}{x - x_1}
is called the point-slope formpoint-slope form for a linear equation. It is sometimes stated in another version by clearing the fraction to get \alert{(x-x_1)}m\amp = \frac{y-y_1}{x-x_1}\alert{(x-x_1)} (x-x_1)m \amp = y - y_1y \amp = y_1 + m(x-x_1)

