subsection.p:
From her two best pictures, she obtains the following information. The total weight of 3 thrushes and 6 robins is 48 ounces, and the total weight of 5 thrushes and 2 robins is 32 ounces. The biologist writes two equations about the photos. She begins by assigning variables to the two unknown quantities: \amp\text{Average weight of a thrush:} ~~t \amp\text{Average weight of a robin:} ~~r In each of the photos,
(\blert{\text{weight of thrushes}}) + (\blert{\text{weight of robins}}) = \blert{\text{total weight}}
Thus 3t + 6r \amp = 485t + 2r \amp =32

