subsection.p:

        3(\alert{4})+ 6(\alert{6}) \amp \stackrel{?}{=} 48\amp\amp \glert{\text{True}} 

        5(\alert{4})+ 2(\alert{6}) \amp \stackrel{?}{=} 32\amp\amp \glert{\text{True}} 

Both equations are true, so we have found the solution: a thrush weighs 4 ounces on average, and a robin weighs 6 ounces.

