statement.p:
Solve each system.
\begin{aligned}[t] y = -x + 5\\ 2x + 2y = 3 \end{aligned}
\begin{aligned}[t] x = \frac{2}{3}y + 3\\ 3x - 2y = 9 \end{aligned}

sidebyside.p:
x \amp = \frac{2}{3}y + 3\amp\amp \glert{\text{Subtract 3.}}  x -3\amp = \frac{2}{3}y \amp\amp \glert{\text{Multiply by }   \frac{3}{2}.}\frac{3}{2}x-\frac{9}{2}\amp = y
For the second equation,
3x - 2y \amp = 9  \amp\amp \glert{\text{Subtract }    3x.}-2y \amp = -3x + 9  \amp\amp \glert{\text{Divide by } -2.}y \amp = \frac{3}{2}x - \frac{9}{2}

