subsection.p:
Next, we find the x-coordinate of the vertex by taking the average of the two x-intercepts.
	x=\frac{1}{2}\left[0+\left(\frac{-b}{a}\right)\right]=\frac{-b}{2a}
Now we have a formula for the x-coordinate of the vertex.

