        y = 2(x - \amp \alert{3})^2 ~ \amp\alert{- 8}\amp \alert{x_v} \amp \alert{y_v}
This equation is an example of the vertex formvertex form for a quadratic function.

assemblage.p:
A quadratic equation ~y=ax^2+bx+c,~a \not=0,~ can be written in the vertex form 
    \blert{y=a(x-x_v)^2+y_v}
where the vertex of the graph is ~(x_v,y_v).

