introduction.p:
Kleiber modeled his data by the power function
P(m) = 73.3m^{0.74}
where P is the metabolic rate and m is the mass of the animal.  Kleiber's rule initiated the use of allometric equationsallometric equations, or power functions of mass, in physiology.

