li.p:
Two lines are parallelparallel if their slopes are equal, that is, if

    \blert{m_1 = m_2}

or if both lines are vertical.

Two lines are perpendicularperpendicular if the product of their slopes is -1, that is, if

    \blert{m_1 m_2 = -1}

or if one of the lines is horizontal and one is vertical.

subsection.p:
Another way to state the condition for perpendicular lines is

    m_2=\frac{-1}{m_1}

Because of this relationship, we often say that the slope of one perpendicular line is the negative reciprocalnegative reciprocal of the other.

