solution.p:
Now we use the point-slope formula with mâ€¯=\dfrac{-1}{2} and (x_1, y_1) = (1, 4).

        y-y_1 \amp=m(x-x_1) 

        y-4 \amp=\frac{-1}{2}(x-1) \amp\amp\glert{\text{Apply the distributive law.}}

        y-4 \amp=\frac{-1}{2}x+\frac{1}{2} \amp\amp\glert{\text{Add 4 to both sides.}}

        y \amp= \frac{-1}{2}x+\frac{9}{2} \amp\amp\glert{\frac{1}{2}+4=\frac{1}{2}+\frac{8}{2}=\frac{9}{2} }

The given line and the perpendicular line are shown in the figure on the above.

